nt to slide rules to smartphones—for recording, storing, and processing information. Beautifully illustrated throughout with previously unstudied and unedited diagrams, Lines of Thought is a historical overview of an important cognitive habit, providing a new window into the world of medieval scholars and their patterns of thinking.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aManuscripts, Medieval. 0aPaleography, Latin 0aPaleography, Latin. 0aPhilosophy, Medieval. 0aSigns and symbols 0aSigns and symbols. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  adiagram, diagramming, diagrams, medieval, historical, history, academic, scholarly, research, recall, remembering, memory, remember, organization, middle ages, time period, era, linguistic, cognitive, theology, philosophy, law, medicine, interdisciplinary, records, paleography, manuscript, signs, symbols, cognition, metaphysics, classroom, legal.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z9783110753851oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226743110423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226743110/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075408-7  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2021